cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the application of deep learning for image classification, specifically for mammogram tumors. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and ensemble methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of visualization techniques to understand the features detected by the neural network, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper mentions the use of ROC AUC, which is a common evaluation metric in neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible category as well.
